{"id":14881452,"mediaExerciseId":"09815c9b-1610-4334-b4f2-57aed30133de","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"14","chapterTitle":"Cost of Capital","groupId":612387,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":488,"solutions":[{"id":5981645,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"Whenever the risk involved with every project is diverse, a company should be using separate costs of capital because of its various operational divisions, whereas if a firm's weighted average cost of capital is being used as the hurdle rate with all divisions, the expected return from the larger division would be larger than the hurdle rate, and funds allocated to such divisions would be larger than the funds allocated to the other divisions, so projected return in this circumstance would also be larger than the SML, even though it should be smaller.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":286,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c017f07e7fe1bdf8315e8dfe562b55e9/c927d4aa92f13c700ecd19e85d071d03/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":145,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c017f07e7fe1bdf8315e8dfe562b55e9/c927d4aa92f13c700ecd19e85d071d03/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"When estimating the cost of capital of multiple divisions, a challenge occurs since the company's entire stocks are traded in the market, making estimating the cost of capital for specific divisions difficult.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c017f07e7fe1bdf8315e8dfe562b55e9/b3313a8fc9578cf9b601b856c0a9cd92/lateximg_large.png","width":1004},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c017f07e7fe1bdf8315e8dfe562b55e9/b3313a8fc9578cf9b601b856c0a9cd92/lateximg.png","width":503}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let's see below there are two methods for determining a rough estimate of each division's cost of capital:\n\n$i)$  A pure-play method is one in which a company looks for a business that operates purely in the very same line of business, calculates its cost of capital, and then changes it to match that company's cost of capital.\n\n$ii)$ The subjective adjustment is a strategy in which the corporation divides projects into risk categories and afterward adjusts the cost of capital accordingly. In this technique, the company's cost of capital is adjusted based on the economy's current economic realities.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":329,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c017f07e7fe1bdf8315e8dfe562b55e9/ddf22f7071f85c9236919b30fb8270e1/lateximg_large.png","width":1041},"regular":{"height":166,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/04/c017f07e7fe1bdf8315e8dfe562b55e9/ddf22f7071f85c9236919b30fb8270e1/lateximg.png","width":520}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"ebe388c6-418c-4cc6-a57d-15d62e9bc2cc","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881453,"exerciseName":"1","page":488,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"88fb4092-110b-40b8-9048-07e4a83a27d5","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-critical-thinking-questions-1-88fb4092-110b-40b8-9048-07e4a83a27d5"},{"id":14881454,"exerciseName":"2","page":488,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"845384f4-e629-410f-8d83-25eee1173ea1","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-critical-thinking-questions-2-845384f4-e629-410f-8d83-25eee1173ea1"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881451,"exerciseName":"9","page":488,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"bc438819-af03-40a3-866f-e8b3387cac1b","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-critical-thinking-questions-9-bc438819-af03-40a3-866f-e8b3387cac1b"},{"id":14881450,"exerciseName":"8","page":487,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b4d11825-ae83-4e6a-bc81-9a299db0af7a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-critical-thinking-questions-8-b4d11825-ae83-4e6a-bc81-9a299db0af7a"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-14-critical-thinking-questions-10-09815c9b-1610-4334-b4f2-57aed30133de"}